2026-04-02 12:55:31 - Agent_20260402124409 - INFO - [+] Agent signaled completion: Reviewed 3 CodeQL results from query 20260402124207 targeting ZipMisc.java. Found 2 confirmed vulnerabilities:

1. **Zip Slip (HIGH) - Line 180**: `ZipMisc.unzip()` uses `entry.getName()` directly in `new File(destinationDir, entry.getName())` without any path traversal validation or canonicalization. A malicious zip with entries like `../../etc/cron.d/backdoor` will write files outside the destination directory. Classic CWE-022 Zip Slip.

2. **Traversal Name Propagation (MEDIUM) - Lines 109-135**: `ZipMisc.modify()` copies zip entries from input to output using `entry.getName()` without sanitization at both the "modified entries" path (line 121, `new ZipEntry(entry.getName())`) and the "unmodified entries" path (line 128, `new ZipEntry(entry)`). Malicious traversal entry names are propagated unchanged into the output zip, creating a poisoned archive that can trigger Zip Slip when subsequently extracted.
